node.text:
@tomcormier quit his high paying engineering job to pursue dropshipping full time. He is now giving back by dedicating his time to helping the average person make a realistic side income from home with Dropshipping. 
Give @tomcormier a follow! 🔥🔥

May be an image of text that says 'Ecom Tom @tomcormier Did you Know that there is a way to dropship without ever building a store or running any ads? Let me oreak it down for you.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @tomcormier. May be an image of text that says 'Ecom Tom @tomcormier The way that most people dropship is incredibly saturated and is usually much more work than what they like to tell you. "Yeah man just build a great website, run profitable ads, and choose a great product. It's easy bro!!!!"'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @tomcormier. May be an image of text that says 'Ecom Tom @tomcormier Anyways, let's cut to the chase. You want to dropship through eBay and Facebook Marketplace All of of the traffic is already there, you don't need to run any ads.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @tomcormier. May be an image of text that says 'Ecom Tom @tomcormier The best part abon it? It's a huge untapped market. Not too many people are using these platforms for dropshipping. Especially the Facebook marketplace.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @tomcormier. May be an image of text that says 'Ecom Tom @tomcormier Now, you're not going to go make a million dollars overnight doing this. But it is an easy way just to make some money on the side or potentially build a business out of it you want to. Personally, I do over $50,000 in sales a month using these platforms every month.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @tomcormier. May be an image of text that says 'Ecom Tom @tomcormier If you want to learn the best strategies around eBay and Facebook Marketplace dropshipping, follow me. I've been doing this for years now and can definitely help you out.'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be an image of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez Does dropshipping still work in 2021? Over the last 3 years, I've generated over $3M in sales. Here's my blueprint to becoming a profitable dropshipper in 2021.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be an image of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez First off, here's how my dropshipping journey started. In college, got introduced to entrepreneurship and started 4 different dropshipping businesses. I ended up failing at all of them and found myself $10,000 in debt...'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be an image of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez I had to get a job and was so close to quitting until unti came across high ticket dropshipping. For the next 8 months, worked 12 hours a day and started making $10k/ month profit. And by now I've generated over $3M in sales. So here's the blueprint.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez 1. Open your LLC High ticket e-commerce is a legitimate business. Before you can close a supplier you need an LLC, a resale certificate, and a Tax ID.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be an image of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez 2. Find products & suppliers I don't sell cheap China products. only sell high-quality high ticket products from US suppliers. Find products worth AT LEAST $500 and suppliers that have less than 10 retailers. Wayfair is a great place to start.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez 3. Create your demo site Create a demo store and list your first demo products. The sole purpose of this is to show suppliers what the store is going to look like so you have a better chance at closing them.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be an image of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez 4. Close suppliers Just like with every other business model you need to know how to sell. Once you find potential suppliers get them on the phone. What helped me close them is to think big and be confident.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be an image of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez 5. Set up Google Ads I choose Google Ads over Facebook Ads because only want to offer my products to people who are already looking for them. Note: You won't get rich after your first Ad. It's all about testing until you find a winner.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez 6. Scale & Automate Hire employees that can take care of customer service and do the day-to- day tasks so you can focus on growing the business and creating your freedom.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 16, 2021 tagging @themichaelopez. May be an image of text that says 'Mikey Lopez @themichaelopez This is how you can build a profitable dropshipping business in 2021. I'm not rich by any means, but I can wake up and do whatever the hell want knowing my money is coming in. If you want more dropshipping tips like that, drop me a follow.'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers Just helped a young military man set up a tax free retirement plan. He's 26. $600 a month. If he never increases the monthly amount, at age 65 he'll have $1,259,207. And, tax-free income of....wait for it... $99,500 a year. For LIFE.'.

node.text:
No other financial planner is putting out information like this.

Go drop @ronocaruthers a follow 🔥

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers Just helped a young military man set up a tax free retirement plan. He's 26. $600 a month. If he never increases the monthly amount, at age 65 he'll have $1,259,207. And, tax-free income of....wait for it... $99,500 a year. For LIFE.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers When he retires from the military at 38, he'll also get about $2,500 a month, and go into corporate or government service. Somewhere in there, we'll probably add another one of these accounts, get him investing up to the match in his 401k, and invest in some real estate.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers I've seen a lot of notes about inflation. Some intelligent, some less so. But, it's a fair point: What WILL $99,500 a year be worth in 39 years? First off, it's tax-free, so whatever rate taxes are at, it's worth that much more.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers Right now, between that and his military pension, he would be in the 22% bracket. And 6% for the state of CA So, on that money, if it WASN'T tax free, he would have to make $138,194 just to net the $99,500 However, at 3% inflation THAT amount is really only worth about $43,635'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers But, the advantage that THIS account has is that he has access to the money before he's 59 1/2. So, he can use the money for: -a house down payment; -a wedding; -Investments; -Even his own kids's education. His other accounts will force him to pay tax and penalties.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers So, it's a fair point. On the other hand... 1.1 1. DELIBERATELY used a much more conservative interest rate than what that plan has historically earned so the real numbers are likely to be (somewhat) higher. 2. It's just ONE piece of his financial plan.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers 3. We're also assuming that he never increases his $600/month contributions.....but his salary and income WILL increase over the next 39 years. So, his contributions to this and other accounts will likely increase as well, but I didn't show that.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers 4. However, for those of you saying that putting $273,600 into an account and getting an income stream of $99,500 a year for the rest of his life is BAD??! He puts in that amount, If he lives to 86, he pulls out $2,189,000 tax free. And still has $1,079,000 in cash.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers 5. And for those of you that are saying: 'WeLl, hE SHoULd Day TraDe AnD mAkE MOrE' Or put it all in stocks. Maybe he will later. Nothing wrong with that either. But saying he's 'guaranteed' to make a 22% return so he shouldn't do this? Yeah. No.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship & Investing💲 on September 15, 2021 tagging @ronocaruthers. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ron Caruthers @roncaruthers A couple more notes on this I used a properly structured Index Universal Life Insurance. Key words: Properly structured. So it literally has the least amount of death benefit possible. We're also contributing to a Roth IRA and he has a TSP.'.
